    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-26T09:24:55+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-26T09:24:55+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-25T23:54:55Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-25T23:54:55Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A low pressure system lies north of Kangaroo Island, with an associated trough over central districts. The low is expected to move north and over the Eyre Peninsula and towards the Flinders district today, weakening as it moves into NSW on Wednesday. A weak ridge of high pressure begins to move across SA later in the week. A cold front is expected to move over the west of SA on Friday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers south of Woomera, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm east of Coober Pedy from the late morning. Winds southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening. Daytime maximum temperatures between 16 and 20.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:40am to 2:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 4 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the morning. Winds southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h turning southerly 20 to 30 km/h in the late morning then decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-28T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Coober Pedy. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-28T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-29T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog east of Stuart Highway. Winds northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h turning west to southwesterly during the morning then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
